Today's daily reading for Wednesday, May 17, 2017 indicates the need to release old relationship baggage and control issues and move into more balanced and harmonious relationships personally and globally. Giving and receiving love, affection and respect can bring back lost harmony. Today's universal number is 5+17+2017 = 14 = 5. The number 5 represents organizations, stability and expertise. Today we may be focusing on regaining some structure and stability back into our lives and relationships. The secret is a balance of giving and receiving then letting go of having to control people, places and things. Consult the inner expert on how to release this energy. Globally, though, we may be looking a the crumbling of organizations and structures that are unstable. Sounds about right, doesn't it? Your personal number for the reading is 16+6+6+8 = 36 = 9. The number 9 represents abundance that results from completions and endings. Clearly old and outdated behaviors, beliefs, systems and organizations will experience a shock. Today marks the beginning of the end for unstable structures personally and globally. Embrace the change, my friends, because in time we will receive so much more abundance and harmony as we rebuild. My Dad has been with me since Thursday - he's visiting because he's ill ... at this moment I am his sole caretaker. We returned to the physician's office today for the 2nd time in just a few days. A nice lady came in to get his vitals. For the Grace of God I'll never know why I asked this question ... in hindsight I believe a higher being was watching over. Out of nowhere I asked her, " Do you have any kiddos?" She stopped typing midstream, gazed over and responded, "I used to, he died in June from leukemia." I kept eye contact, I held silence for a few moments before I said, "I am deeply sorry!" She was tearful and I believe a part of her wanted to "save me, her and/or us." She quickly an enthusiastically asked, "How was your Mother's Day?" I replied it was tolerable this year, I didn't even cry. I have yearned for a child and family but it has not happened." She returned the words I am sorry. We had a moment where we met each other deeply and profoundly. I am reminded of the quote: "...people can only meet you as deeply as they've met themselves." -Matt Kahn | Grief and loss are real and we need to stay in that space, hold silence and realize it is within that silent vessel that the experience of being seen and (at least partially) understood can reveal itself.

You love to give and it is part of who you are however too much giving leads to imbalance and struggle. Look around you and within and ask if you feel depleted, resentful or out of balance. When your energies get dangerously low Spirit will try to get your attention with signs, tics and leeches, flat batteries, clocks stopping etc. all external warnings to recharge. You may also notice a feeling of running low on energy, time or money. Remember nothing runs out in this abundant universe. It's  time to receive to balance your giving nature. This may call for a change in life style or belief system so you don't become ill or drained beyond repair.  Shift to allow balance. Let others give to you, best of all give to yourself ..only you can change the balance in your life. When you do, you'll notice that the world becomes more generous . Be sure to open your heart and mind to receive those gifts . Whatever you do don't turn them away! The universe is always listening and reflecting your energy and actions. When you open yourself to receive and balance giving evenly.
